<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
    Bus:  The Country Bus Station next to the County Hospital is the main station for buses arriving from outside the city.  Services 76 and 76A Hereford City Centre – Bartonsham circular will link the hospital with the City Bus Station.<br/><br/>Train:  The main Hereford Railway Station is approximately half a mile from the County Hospital.  Taxis are available outside the station.


</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>There is a ‘drop off point’ by the main entrance.  Parking is limited, however, there is a “pay on foot” system at the and the scale of charges is clearly displayed.<br/><br/>Disabled Parking<br/><br/>There are a limited number of disabled spaces available in front of the hospital.</p>
